I find this design really weird. Why would one be an instance but not the other? The expectation is that either they are both instances or they are both non-instances. Also note that instance loops are *supposed* to be fine in Lean 4
I assumed that avoiding the instance loop was the reason this instance hadn't been declared in the first place, though maybe that was just a holdover from Lean 3. I'll turn it into an instance then.
It seems reasonable/preferrable to have this direct instance for symmetry, expectability and possibly performance

I moved the stuff about `LinearOrder` to the top of the file so I didn't have to open the namespace twice. Honestly it'd probably be better to move it to the common file on `Is*Archimedean` once that exists.

```suggestion
  âŸ¨fun  _ => isPredArchimedean_of_isSuccArchimedean,
    fun  _ => isSuccArchimedean_of_isPredArchimedeanâŸ©
```
is much more robust
